Home Assure Plus
The Right Solutions For The Right Reasons
HOME ASSURE PLUS is an exclusive set of eight services offered by 4Sight Inspections and is included with every Home Inspection at no extra charge. You will not find this level of commitment or confidence in Home Inspection Service anywhere else.

A sample of what HOME ASSURE PLUS provides:
Re-visit*
If repairs are negotiated as a direct result of the inspection performed and the inspection report provided by 4Sight Inspections we will revisit the property at your request and at a mutually convenient time to re-inspect the contractually repaired components to ensure the repair is complete and satisfactory.

Walk-a-way***
If there are major concerns found with the inspected house that cause you to walk away from the purchase agreement I will inspect the next home you place an offer on at half price. i.e. if second home had a rate of $375 then you would only pay $185.

30 Day Warranty
We offer a 30 Day Warranty for structural and mechanical components in the home at no extra charge.

profile:
Baeumler Approved and a Certified Master Inspector, Bryce Rankin believes that knowing your home is key to making a good and safe investment for both you and your family. During the home inspection process clients are encouraged to follow along and ask questions. Being involved in this process gives clients a much better understanding of how the home operates and how to maintain it over the years.
Our detailed Home Inspections reports provide our clients with all the necessary information to make an informed home purchase. With digital reporting it is quick and easy to share your report with family, friends, or contractors to aid in any work or opinions that may be required to move forward comfortably with your investment. Technology is key. Thermal Imaging and Moisture Detection equipment used on all of our inspections can reveal defects that cannot be seen by the human eye. Revealing potential trouble spots throughout the home that can lead to significant cost and frustration down the road. In many cases these defects are hidden from view with a fresh coat of paint, drywall, or storage. Whether a home buyer, seller, or owner we can help. Online booking through our website is available 24/7 or you can contact Bryce Rankin at anytime to discuss your home inspection needs.

Due To The Covid-19 Pandemic, 

Wallbank Home Inspections Have Implemented The Government of Canada COVID-19 Recommendations To Our Normal Process Of A Home Inspection To Ensure The Health & Safety Of Our Home Inspectors, Clients, Friends & Family.

We At Wallbank Home Inspections Take Your Safety Seriously, Our Inspectors Wear New Masks, Gloves & Sanitize All Equipment Prior & After Leaving Your Home.
Our Inspectors Are Double Vaccinated + Booster, Experienced, Detailed & Provide First Class Customer Service.

We Respect Your Privacy, Your Family And Your Home, We Also Remove Our Boots At The Front Door! 

We Keep Our Findings In Perspective, The Inspection Usually Lasts 2 1/2 Hours, It Will Consist Of Physically Inspecting And Reporting On The Condition Of The Systems And Components Of The Home. This Consists Of The Structural Foundation, Roof, Exterior, Electrical, Heating & Cooling, Plumbing, Insulation, Ventilation, And Interior Of The Home.

profile:
A professional inspection will significantly reduce your risk and help make the entire home buying process easier and less stressful. Legacy Home Inspections really enjoys helping our clients. In this process, customer service is our highest priority.

Legacy Home Inspections is an independently owned and operated home inspection business. We offer the highest quality of customer service in the industry. With more than 19 years of experience in the construction and home inspection industry we have performed thousands of inspections since 2004. We have the experience, training and knowledge, to provide you with the security and peace of mind you are looking for. We are proud to be your inspection service provider. Whether you are buying or selling, we can help you through the whole process with confidence. A home is the single largest investment and asset that most people own. We offer a premium service with detailed and unbiased reports to ensure that you have an accurate understanding of the subject property. We strive to continually raise the bar in the building inspection industry.

We offer more than just a look into our client's home, we also want to ensure that you know your home. Our goal is to have you understand your property. Our home inspections are intended to educate by giving you a needed understanding of the property, an overview of how the systems in the home work, how the systems of the home work in conjunction with each other, and how they should be maintained throughout the change of seasons and over the years.

Why choose Legacy Home Inspections? Because we care.

profile: Dive Deep Home Inspections is a residential home inspection company made up of Certified Home Inspectors who have residential construction and renovation experience. Inspectors who know how the systems of your home should actually function. Your home is the largest investment you will make in you lifetime. Whether you are just looking to buy, preparing to sell the one you have, or maybe just looking to make sure its well maintained, let us have a look. Dive Deep Home Inspections only works with Certified Home Inspectors who have past residential construction or renovation experience. We know homes from the ground up. A proper home inspection, sometimes called a Field Performance Review, consists of a visual inspection and tests using the standard operating controls, of the major systems in your home. Systems which include roofing, structure, exterior, interior and insulation, plumbing, electrical, and of course your heating and air conditioning. Don't trust such a detailed inspection to just anyone. Our certified and experienced inspectors know how these systems should function. All inspections are documented in a report, that includes full colour pictures, and diagrams and links that help you to understand your inspectors findings. Your report comes to you by email within 24 hours and you will have access to your inspectors for as long as you need for questions and/or explanations. Let us Dive Deep into your home!

profile:
Mike Inspects is a Burlington based InterNACHI-certified Home Inspection Company. As your home inspector, Mike will conduct a thorough, professional, visual inspection of your property from top to bottom. Every home inspection comes with a free home maintenance book and our Added Value Package.

______________

This Home Maintenance Book is 100 pages in full colour and full of helpful tips on how to maintain your home all at no extra cost to you. It will reveal all that you need to know before you list your Burlington home, Hamilton home or Oakville home for sale.

______________

Mike Inspects is own and operated by Mike Oliveira a Certified Home Inspector currently living locally in the city of Burlington. Mike is originally from Oakville and knows the area well. He is devoted to his community and will give 100% when inspecting your home. 

______________

Make absolutely sure that your dream home is not hiding any unwanted surprises that could be expensive to fix after you buy. Mike will provide you with peace of mind you need to go through with one of the largest purchases in your life. 

______________

Backed by $10,000 HONOUR GUARANTEE, FREE With Every Home Inspection


Mike provides the following additional inspection services such as:

______________
										
PRE-LISTING
							
Eventually, your buyers are going to conduct an inspection. You may as well know what they are going to find by getting there first. Having an inspection performed ahead of time helps in many other ways: 

-It allows you to see your home through the eyes of a critical third-party. It helps you to price your home realistically. 
-It permits you to make repairs ahead of time so that defects will not become negotiating stumbling blocks later. There is no delay in obtaining the Use and Occupancy permit. 
-You have the time to get reasonably priced contractors or make the repairs yourself if qualified. 
-It may encourage the buyer to waive the inspection contingency. It may alert you of items of immediate personal concern, such as radon gas or active termite infestation. 
-It may relieve prospects concerns and suspicions. It reduces your liability by adding professional supporting documentation to your disclosure statement. 

Alerting you to immediate safety issues before agents and visitors tour your home.

Copies of the inspection report along with receipts for any repairs should be made available to potential buyers. 	

______________

THERMAL IMAGING 

Thermal imaging or infrared camera inspections can provide valuable information regarding moisture, energy loss, roof leaks, electrical overloads and even wood destroying organisms in homes and buildings.

______________

IAC2 CERTIFIED

International Association of Indoor Air Consultants (IAC2) is the non-profit, certifying body for home and building inspectors who have fulfilled certain educational and testing requirements including those in the area of indoor air quality.

______________

MOVEIN CERTIFIED

MoveInCertified homes have been pre-inspected by InterNACHI certified inspectors and the sellers confirm that there are no major systems in need of immediate repair or replacement and no known safety hazards.

______________

MOLD is a part of the natural environment.  
Outdoors, molds play a part in nature by breaking down dead organic matter such as fallen leaves and dead trees, but indoors, mold growth should be avoided. Proper inspection, health risks and prevention should be considered.												

Dedicated to quality and the very best in Home Inspection Services. Mike is passionate about providing his clients with detailed remoting, and high-quality Home Inspections.  For more information or to book an appointment with Mike Inspects visit the website https://www.mikeinspects.ca or you can call or send a text message anytime if you have questions (289)208-2554.

_______________

Connect with us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Mike-Inspects-266472477384746/
LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/mike-oliveira-752432179/
